{
  "timestamp": "2026-07-23T14:09:27Z",
  "title": "Signed, installable Wellframe Coach .mcpb bundle",
  "type": "feature",
  "userRequest": "I want to get to a MCPB I can test on my machine.",
  "description": "Made the Wellframe Coach MCP server build into a signed, Claude-Desktop-installable .mcpb in one command. `npm run bundle` packs a production-only tree (staged, so the dev tree is never mutated and the bundle drops from ~50MB to ~10MB unpacked), smoke-tests all 9 tools against missing/empty/populated databases by unpacking the real packed bundle, and self-signs with a stable local cert. Extracted the two silent-failure-prone parsers (signature-block reader, desktop-schema scraper) into a tested bundle module; documented that mcpb 2.1.2's own `verify` reports every bundle as unsigned (node-forge p7.verify throws), so a self-sign is tamper-evidence, not publisher verification, and verify-signature.mjs checks the real PKCS#7 with openssl. In passing: fixed the mcp-server tests corrupting the repo's vitest JSON gate (node:test → vitest, unblocking the whole suite for codeyam), added a dev-only Vite CSP relaxation so desktop scenarios can be captured (production Tauri CSP untouched), and brought mcp-server into codeyam alignment by registering its functions and thinning fatigueInputs into tested pure helpers.",
